In Isaac, large-scale parallel processing of robot data requires converting inputs into tensors. We are still evaluating two possible paths:
1. Action (func call) > predefined joint target > merged tensor > Omniverse
2. Joint target from synapse > merged tensor > Omniverse
The latter would cause significant changes to the existing miner processing logic.

If we adopt the latter approach, miners will need to output each joint target of the agent(no move_xxx anymore). This is quite different from the traditional AI (LLM) area and would significantly increase the development difficulty for subnet miners.

new_immunity_period = (new_commit_reveal_period x tempo - old_commit_reveal_period x tempo) + old_immunity_period

Commit Reveal interval, otherwise the immunity period will expire before a given miner's scores are available, and they may be deregistered without having their work counted.

When creating a new subnet, ensure that the miner immunity period is larger than the commit reveal interval. When updating the immunity period or commit reveal interval hyperparameters for a subnet, use the following formula:

That is, for a new miner, the first estimates will come after about 5 hours.

- Some NPCs can now move around: Previously stationary characters will now travel through different areas. Agents will need to locate and approach them as part of their tasks.
